The paper focuses on analyzing the social impact of a person's communities on their mobility, which falls under the category of social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to predict users' future movement, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of a measure to characterize a person's social diversity, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also deals with privacy concerns related to location data, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper uses real-life datasets to demonstrate its findings, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
